{
  "text": "There are numerous definitions of teams, most of which include the following criteria: small size [CITATION_1] , defined membership [CITATION_2] , shared responsibility for outcomes [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , some interdependence or relationship and common goals [CITATION_5] , commitment to collaboration and joint accountability [CITATION_6] ), a common purpose for which they are mutually accountable [CITATION_7] and (some) shared accountability [CITATION_8] . The key characteristics of teams are thus defined membership, a common goal, interdependence and some shared accountability for goal achievement. A business management team can thus be defined as \"a small set of people within an organisation who have a common goal and are dependent on one another to achieve that goal\".",
